                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Nov. 27 (PTI): Delhi High Court has asked judges to be vigilant following an alarming increase in the number of convicts going untraceable after being granted bail.          
	There is an alarming and sinister increase in instances where the routine is to file an appeal, apply and be enlarged on bail and thereafter to become untraceable, the court said.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): An elderly woman and her daughter were allegedly beaten to death at their home in suburban Malad. The victims, identified as Anthonita Astris, 65, and Peeti Varghese, 40, were hit with an iron rod late on Thursday night, police said.                   
	 Chennai: An old man died after a Ganesh idol sculpted out of ice fell on him at a wedding reception in Chennai on Thursday evening.           
	The idol, weighing 20kg, had been placed at the entrance of the wedding hall at Tambaram, a Chennai suburb. Harikrishnan, 70, the father of the hall watchman, was having an ice cream, seated on a chair near the structure, when it fell on him. He suffered head injuries and died in hospital.           
	Police said the Ganesh, which had been placed at the entrance in the morning, had melted and its base had become weak, leading to the crash.           
	The wedding ceremony, however,was held on Friday after a puja was conducted at the site of the accident.                   
	 Guruvayur (PTI): Twenty-five elephants marched in a procession to pay floral tributes to Guruvayur Kesavan on the 33rd death anniversary of the Kerala temple tusker. The elephant had served the Guruvayur temple for nearly 50 years.                  
	 Kurukshetra (PTI): Four crocodiles were caught in Kurukshetra in Uttar Pradesh on Friday and handed over to wildlife officials. The crocodiles had got trapped in a pond after straying from a nearby canal. The villagers found the reptiles after they had scared off some buffaloes.                                                                                                                                              
